{"author":"RebarBotNava","data":{"alias":"untameable-appalling-jaguarundi","description":"## Reproduction Steps\nThe rebar review bot (compose-review-bot-1 on the rebar-gerrit EC2 host) clones each change into /tmp/rebar-gate-snapshots to review it. These snapshots are never garbage-collected, so the 30G root disk fills to 100%.\n\n## Expected vs Actual\n- Expected: review workspace is bounded / cleaned per review.\n- Actual: /tmp/rebar-gate-snapshots grew to 14G; root fs hit 100%; clone_change_ref failed with 'No space left on device', which the voter surfaces as [LLM-Review: BLOCK — coverage-gap (review-error)] on EVERY change (observed on 452, 458, 461, 462). This fail-closed vetoes unrelated changes.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] The review-bot's per-change clone/snapshot workspace is bounded or cleaned after each review (e.g. rm the snapshot on completion, or a periodic prune).\n- [ ] A disk-usage guard/alarm so the host does not silently reach 100%.\n- [ ] Document the manual recovery (docker builder prune + clear /tmp/rebar-gate-snapshots) in an infra runbook.\n\n## Discovered\nWhile landing epic breaded-ammonitic-elephant: change 458's LLM-Review persistently returned coverage-gap (review-error). Root cause via SSM was the full host disk, not the change.","id":"9d7c-17b3-b637-45ac","parent_id":"","priority":2,"tags":[],"ticket_type":"bug","title":"review-bot host disk fills up (rebar-gate-snapshots leak) -> coverage-gap review-errors"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1783656139743562001,"uuid":"b6e2962b-a1ed-426d-8ff5-cc21fd5bf9a1"}